Product Description

Quality Fresh & Clean Air for the Home

BioShield HVAC UVC Light

Providing a healthy lifestyle through UV technology.

Why BioShield?

Replaceable UVC Bulbs

All BioShield devices use UVC bulbs that can be easily replaced when needed.

Get 10% off replacement bulbs by joining Guardian Club.

CE Certifications

Certified and the preferred choice by HVAC specialists and contractors, BioShield devices are easy to install and use for all types of spaces.

Quality Air

Whether the device is configured to your HVAC system or plugged into an outlet, quality air is easy to achieve with BioShield.

Ozone Free

Designed with health and safety in mind, BioShield devices are ozone free utilizing only UV technology in making air clean to breathe.

Safety First

Easy Installation & Use


Made for easy use and installation, BioShield cleans the air through the use of UVC technology. All devices come with installation guides and template stickers to guide you in every step.

Replaceable bulbs are available for every device to ensure quality fresh and clean air at your home all year round.

How long do UVC bulbs usually last?

BioShield UVC bulbs are rated to last up to 8,000 hours. However, we generally recommend replacing bulbs at least twice a year as their effectiveness diminishes over time.

Is it normal for UVC bulbs to emit a certain odor when the lamp is turned on?

It is completely normal for UVC lights to emit a faint odor, especially when they are first used. This odor is usually due to the heating of dust particles that might have settled on the light during manufacturing or storage.

Can I install BioShield devices on my own?

Yes, all our devices are designed for easy installation and use. Guides and template stickers are included in every order to help you with installation.

We recommend wearing safety gloves when touching the UVC bulb to avoid irritation on the skin.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Bradley
5.0 out of 5 stars Great product; confusing acronyms for the different models
Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
Style Name: ACVerified Purchase
I've got two HVACs and one has been consuming ballasts and bulbs while the other one chugs along without issue for 8 years. I did some research and the more reliable one is the exact same ballast as this item. I ordered the DC version thinking "direct current" would be the one that you wire to the 24v transformer in the air handler - nope that one is the wall plug version. I exchanged it for the AC version, which I would think is "alternating current", but sure enough, it's the one that gets wired to the 24v transformer. The box on the AC version even says "Wall Outlet Adapter" so I don't know what that's all about. That confusion now behind me, the install was simple as I swapped the troublesome ballast for this new one and connected the two wires. Based on prior experience I expect this to perform well for many years, but I'll update the review if it fails prematurely. Also, be sure not look at these bulbs when they're on...it only takes a couple min to burn your eyes it's a bit scary (yes, I did this the first time I changed the bulbs).
